==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Whew
<hw>Whew</hw> <pr>(hw⟦umac⟧)</pr>, <pos>n. & interj.</pos> <def>A sound
like a half-formed whistle, expressing astonishment, scorn, or
dislike.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Whew duck</b></col>, <cd>the European widgeon.</cd>
<mark>[Prov. Eng.]</mark></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Whew</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Whew
<hw>Whew</hw>, <pos>v. i.</pos> <def>To whistle with a shrill pipe, like
a plover.</def> <mark>[Prov. Eng. & Scot.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Whewellite</ent>⟦br⟧
